cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the use of dropout as a regularizer in neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also explores the theoretical properties of dropout, which is related to optimization (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper focuses on linear classification, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS).
